	<div class="expert-content-text">
		<p>To see all New York City Travel articles, <a href="http://gonyc.about.com/" data-component="contentBioPage" data-source="channelhomepage" data-type="site.displayName" data-ordinal="1" itemprop="url">click here</a>.</p>
		<p><p>Heather Cross has been About.com's New York City Travel Expert since 2002. Heather explores her hometown so she can give you the best first-hand advice possible. You might even spot her running around New York City -- she's always visiting museums, taking guided tours and eating at great restaurants so that she can point her readers toward the best the city has to offer.</p>

<p>In addition to sharing her advice on About.com, Heather offers customized travel planning services through <a href="http://www.vacationsbyheather.com/new-york-city-vacations/" zT="-o1/XJ" target="_blank">Vacations By Heather</a>.</p>

<p><strong>Become a Fan</strong>: <a href="http://www.facebook.com/newyorkcitytravel" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">New York City Travel on Facebook</a><br>
<strong>Follow Me</strong> <a href="http://twitter.com/NYCTravel" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">New York City Travel on Twitter</a><br>
<strong>Email Me:</strong> <a href="mailto:gonyc@vacationsbyheather.com?subject=Message%20from%20NYC%20Travel%20on%20About.com" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">gonyc@vacationsbyheather.com</a><br>
<strong>PR/Press Inquiries:</strong> <a href="mailto:press@vacationsbyheather.com?subject=Press%2FPR%3A%20NYC%20Travel%20on%20About.com" zT="-o1/XL" target="_blank">press@vacationsbyheather.com</a></p>

<p>Heather's New York City expertise has been featured on <em>Today in New York</em> and ESPN 1050.</p></p>
		<h5>Experience</h5>
		<p>After college, Heather moved to New York City where she learned the ins and outs of life in New York City. She&#39;s lived in the city since then and has played tour guide to numerous family members and friends visiting from out of town, and made the &quot;Big City&quot; feel a whole lot less intimidating.
<p>Whether she&#39;s riding the subway, taking a cab, or exploring on her own two feet, she&#39;s always thinking about what to share with her readers. Now that she has two kids to keep her company exploring, she also has a lot of insight to share about traveling with kids and making New York City fun and manageable for families.</p></p>
			<h5>Education</h5>
			<p><p>Heather graduated from the University of Connecticut with a B.A. in English.</p></p>
			<h5>Heather Cross</h5>
			<p>I love New York City, and I love showing other people all that there is to love about New York. From museums and guided tours to stores and restaurants, I&#39;ll try just about anything so that I can share my experience with you. I hope that my first-hand knowledge of New York City&#39;s attractions and experiences can make your time in New York City even better than you imagined.</p>
	</div>

